<br>
Then, in a few more steps, you get some modifier to it, say Epic_aug_1, then epic_aug_2, etc...  something that is more of a progression. <br>
<br>
The first epics were good, but they were setup to be nearly impossible but to a few sets of folks.  It wasn't until much later in the life of the game that many people were able to fairly readily make a strong effort to obtain them.  And, even now, you still need 25ish people for most of the hard parts of the epic (assuming yer not Time'ish, cause if you are, you don't want the epic anyway).  <br>
<br>
I'd like to see more group oriented content and definately LESS camping.  Stuff like Phinny is just stupid.  He's an easy mob with a long spawn and a rare drop.  That's not fun, it's just tedious.<br>
<br>
Anyway.  Suggestion:<br>
- Epic should scale upwards as you do parts of the quest<br>
- Parts should be available in some single-group content, no matter how hard.<br>
<br>
Hunt well, <br>
Wyndaria. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keiz>Keiz</A></span><br> Posts: 697<br> <font color=#330000>(6/18/04 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19518.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sleinad.homestead.com/files/keiz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Buildable</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>hey, if they wanna make it good enough that its going to be class defining 2 expansions from now, more power to em.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
